history.content: Grad courses are seldom if ever webcast.

children.subject: Alternatively, you could take Garg's 194 (Cryptography) which does not conflict with 189.
127 also is at the same time -_-
oh I'm sorry, this is a weak point of whoever was scheduling these courses :(

history.content:
I really wanted to take CS 276 (Cryptography) next semester, but it conflicts with CS 189. If I don't take CS 276 now, I probably won't get another chance. I know it's not as important as ML, but I am personally really interested in it.

I have a few options, what would you suggest?

1) Take both. Webcast one. 

Pros: Get to take both classes

Cons: Miss out on either Chiesa or Sahai's lectures.

2) Take 276 now, 189 next semester.

Pros: Get to take 276

Cons: Learn less ML, which is most important than crypto (at least for me), since I have to push back EE 127 / CS 281A / etc.

Be of less help to my research project b/c I don't know ML (it uses ML)

3) Take 189 now, don't take 276

Pros: Learn more ML, contribute more to my research

Cons: Miss out on a great course.

I'm leaning towards option 1 and webcasting 189. 

What do you recommend? Will 276 be webcasted (it's not in @3862)? Thank you!
